msgid "Those functions are (usually) defined in <placeholder-1/> files placed in the <placeholder-2/> directory by packages. Problems can arise when you need to regenerate the <placeholder-3/> files, because the functions used by the <placeholder-4/> file can be defined in an <placeholder-5/> macro file which isn't installed on the user's system. This is the case for example for some optional features which require libraries and are disabled by <placeholder-6/> flags. If the <placeholder-7/> files aren't installed in the user's system, the <placeholder-8/> step will fail."
